00:06:57.660 --> 00:06:59.130
than what church we went to.

00:07:04.380 --> 00:07:06.360
SHANE SMITH: So we're on our
way down here to colonial

00:07:06.360 --> 00:07:09.630
Juarez, which is in northern
Mexico, in Chihuahua state.

00:07:09.630 --> 00:07:13.250
A lot of people may know that
Romney and his family are

00:07:13.250 --> 00:07:14.270
actually from here.

00:07:14.270 --> 00:07:17.310
His father was actually born
here in a Mormon colony.

00:07:17.310 --> 00:07:19.730
But maybe what they don't know
is that these Mormon colonies

00:07:19.730 --> 00:07:23.160
are still here, and they're
actually fighting the narco

00:07:23.160 --> 00:07:26.150
cartels, the drug cartels, that
run this whole region.

00:07:26.150 --> 00:07:27.440
They're standing up, and
they're fighting the

00:07:27.440 --> 00:07:30.390
kidnapping and the violence
and the crime.

00:07:30.390 --> 00:07:33.100
So the question is, what are
the Mormons doing down in

00:07:33.100 --> 00:07:36.990
Mexico in the first place?

00:07:36.990 --> 00:07:41.100
Mormons originally came down to
Mexico in the late 1800s,

00:07:41.100 --> 00:07:43.750
after the American government
forced the Mormon church to

00:07:43.750 --> 00:07:44.850
ban polygamy.

00:07:44.850 --> 00:07:48.110
The problem with this is that
Joseph Smith, the prophet of

00:07:48.110 --> 00:07:51.240
the religion, held that polygamy
was actually a divine

00:07:51.240 --> 00:07:51.980
commandment.

00:07:51.980 --> 00:07:54.970
He believed that you can only
reach the highest level of the

00:07:54.970 --> 00:07:58.730
celestial kingdom, or heaven, if
you were actually a partner

00:07:58.730 --> 00:07:59.480
in a plural marriage.

00:07:59.480 --> 00:08:02.160
So basically, the more wives
you had, the better

00:08:02.160 --> 00:08:03.280
heaven would be.

00:08:03.280 --> 00:08:06.145
And rather than give up their
place in heaven, many moved

00:08:06.145 --> 00:08:09.730
down to Mexico to continue to
practice polygamy, and thereby

00:08:09.730 --> 00:08:12.090
assure their place
in the afterlife.

00:08:12.090 --> 00:08:15.010
Here in the seclusion of the
Mexican desert, they could

00:08:15.010 --> 00:08:18.220
practice all the standard Mormon
rituals like baptizing

00:08:18.220 --> 00:08:21.260
the dead or wearing magic
underwear, but also the more

00:08:21.260 --> 00:08:22.950
controversial plural marriage.

00:08:22.950 --> 00:08:26.180
Or, as we were soon to find
out, the outright insane

00:08:26.180 --> 00:08:28.660
practice of blood atonement.

00:08:28.660 --> 00:08:31.970
So after about five hours of
some very nervous driving and

00:08:31.970 --> 00:08:35.049
a couple of very thorough stops
at military checkpoints,

00:08:35.049 --> 00:08:37.520
not to mention two stops at
drive-through liquor stores to

00:08:37.520 --> 00:08:41.179
calm our very jangling nerves,
we finally arrived at the

00:08:41.179 --> 00:08:42.239
Mormon promised land.

