He was a straight up
fucking lunatic.

00:11:17.570 --> 00:11:22.130
Now, Ervil not only had 13 wives
and over 50 children,

00:11:22.130 --> 00:11:24.550
but he also used own family,
including his

00:11:24.550 --> 00:11:27.720
own kids, as assassins.

00:11:27.720 --> 00:11:30.420
Dubbed "the Mormon Manson,"
Ervil and his family were

00:11:30.420 --> 00:11:32.840
suspects in over 40 murders.

00:11:32.840 --> 00:11:34.950
SHANE SMITH: Joel LeBaron was
killed by his own brother,

00:11:34.950 --> 00:11:37.070
Ervil, because of
blood atonement.

00:11:37.070 --> 00:11:37.440
BRENT LABARON: Yes.

00:11:37.440 --> 00:11:40.260
Well, Ervil tried to take over
the church, and he started

00:11:40.260 --> 00:11:42.860
claiming blood atonement,
the right to kill

00:11:42.860 --> 00:11:43.650
in the name of God.

00:11:43.650 --> 00:11:47.090
If you oppose him, he has
the right to kill you.

00:11:47.090 --> 00:11:49.960
Once Ervil snapped, he just
went on a killing spree.

00:11:49.960 --> 00:11:52.540
He had his daughters
killed, his wives

00:11:52.540 --> 00:11:54.690
killed, his sons killed.

00:11:54.690 --> 00:11:56.240
And it just went from there.

00:11:56.240 --> 00:11:57.810
He went haywire.

00:11:57.810 --> 00:12:00.220
SHANE SMITH: So Ervil goes on
this killing spree across

00:12:00.220 --> 00:12:02.180
Mexico and the United States.

00:12:02.180 --> 00:12:04.890
And at one point, the Secret
Service is after him because

00:12:04.890 --> 00:12:07.260
he threatens to kill
President Carter.

00:12:07.260 --> 00:12:11.170
They finally captured Ervil in
1979 and sent him to prison.

00:12:11.170 --> 00:12:13.000
And all the killing
stops, right?

00:12:13.000 --> 00:12:13.960
Wrong.

00:12:13.960 --> 00:12:17.090
SHANE SMITH: And then after he
dies in jail, people keep on

00:12:17.090 --> 00:12:18.060
killing for him.

00:12:18.060 --> 00:12:21.060
BRENT LABARON: He killed up
to 25 people after he died

00:12:21.060 --> 00:12:23.560
because he left a sort of hit
list, and they kept killing.

00:12:23.560 --> 00:12:24.030
SHANE SMITH: They
kept killing?

00:12:24.030 --> 00:12:24.820
BRENT LABARON: Yes.

00:12:24.820 --> 00:12:25.350
They did.

00:12:25.350 --> 00:12:27.160
SHANE SMITH: Now, as Brent is
telling me all this, I had to

00:12:27.160 --> 00:12:30.290
keep in mind that this blood
atonement killing spree isn't

00:12:30.290 --> 00:12:32.640
taking place in the
1880s or anything.

00:12:32.640 --> 00:12:35.410
This is all happening
in the 1980s.

00:12:35.410 --> 00:12:36.820
BRENT LABARON: My grandfather
ran from him

00:12:36.820 --> 00:12:38.720
for probably 10 years.

00:12:38.720 --> 00:12:41.100
I mean, he chased my grandpa
clear to Nicaragua.

00:12:41.100 --> 00:12:43.980
SHANE SMITH: Your great uncle
was trying to kill your

00:12:43.980 --> 00:12:44.235
grandfather.

00:12:44.235 --> 00:12:45.202
BRENT LABARON: Yeah.

00:12:45.202 --> 00:12:47.920
Verlan M. LeBaron died in a
car accident right out of

00:12:47.920 --> 00:12:48.870
Mexico City.

00:12:48.870 --> 00:12:52.270
A lot of people have been
skeptical that actually Ervil

00:12:52.270 --> 00:12:53.680
had something to do with it.

00:12:53.680 --> 00:12:58.130
And his last recorded words
were, brother, it looks like

00:12:58.130 --> 00:12:59.720
we've been ran off the road.

00:12:59.720 --> 00:13:00.220
SHANE SMITH: Wow.

00:13:00.220 --> 00:13:01.720
That's some crazy shit.

00:13:01.720 --> 00:13:02.630
BRENT LABARON: Yeah.

00:13:02.630 --> 00:13:06.160
It's just a modern day
Cain and Abel here.

00:13:06.160 --> 00:13:08.040
SHANE SMITH: Do you think that
that's one of the reasons why?

00:13:08.040 --> 00:13:11.150
Because you had this sort of
familial civil war you got

00:13:11.150 --> 00:13:14.240
tighter as a family, So when
the narcos came after your

00:13:14.240 --> 00:13:15.740
family, you were sort
of tougher?

00:13:15.740 --> 00:13:16.940
BRENT LABARON: Oh, definitely.

00:13:16.940 --> 00:13:19.610
Everyone was a watchman.

00:13:19.610 --> 00:13:21.510
SHANE SMITH: Now, what he's
saying here is that because of

00:13:21.510 --> 00:13:25.000
Ervil, everyone in the LeBaron
clan watched out

00:13:25.000 --> 00:13:25.860
for everyone else.

00:13:25.860 --> 00:13:27.870
So when the cartels kidnapped
one of their

00:13:27.870 --> 00:13:30.330
own, they were ready.

00:13:30.330 --> 00:13:34.860
Eric LeBaron was only 16 when
he was abducted and held for

00:13:34.860 --> 00:13:37.200
$1 million ransom.

00:13:37.200 --> 00:13:38.280
You didn't pay the ransom.

00:13:38.280 --> 00:13:39.890
BRENT LABARON: We didn't
pay the ransom.

00:13:39.890 --> 00:13:41.700
SHANE SMITH: Even if you could
get the money and paid it,

00:13:41.700 --> 00:13:42.690
they're just going
to keep doing it.

00:13:42.690 --> 00:13:43.830
BRENT LABARON: They're just
going to keep coming

00:13:43.830 --> 00:13:44.550
and keep doing it.

00:13:44.550 --> 00:13:46.600
SHANE SMITH: They'll just use
the money to buy more guns and

00:13:46.600 --> 00:13:47.730
get more powerful.

00:13:47.730 --> 00:13:48.530
BRENT LABARON: Exactly.

00:13:48.530 --> 00:13:51.640
If we don't sever the head off
this monster right now, it's

00:13:51.640 --> 00:13:52.800
just going to get worse.

00:13:52.800 --> 00:13:55.330
We had to go to the government
and say, hey.

00:13:55.330 --> 00:13:57.490
You won't allow us
to bear arms.

00:13:57.490 --> 00:14:00.020
But you're supposed
to protect us.

00:14:00.020 --> 00:14:01.930
SHANE SMITH: The protest forced
the government to put

00:14:01.930 --> 00:14:03.520
pressure on the kidnappers.

00:14:03.520 --> 00:14:06.470
And as is quite rare in these
situations, Eric was returned

00:14:06.470 --> 00:14:09.050
unharmed after paying
no ransom.

00:14:09.050 --> 00:14:12.850
However, it also served to
enrage the local drug Lord,

00:14:12.850 --> 00:14:15.370
named "El Rikin," who only lived
eight miles down the

00:14:15.370 --> 00:14:17.740
road from Colonia LeBaron.

00:14:17.740 --> 00:14:21.185
Now, this is a narco who loves
drugs so much that he actually

00:14:21.185 --> 00:14:24.710
massacred 18 people trying to
get off the stuff at a drug

00:14:24.710 --> 00:14:25.555
rehab center.

00:14:25.555 --> 00:14:27.945
And now, he's after
the LeBarons.

00:14:35.490 --> 00:14:37.310
NEWS ANCHOR 1: Two more
Americans dead as a result of

00:14:37.310 --> 00:14:38.740
the violence in Mexico.

00:14:38.740 --> 00:14:42.470
Those victims gunned down this
week by drug cartel killers.

00:14:42.470 --> 00:14:44.540
NEWS ANCHOR 2: We've done a lot
of stories about polygamy

00:14:44.540 --> 00:14:47.570
and a lot of stories about
Mexican drug cartel violence.

00:14:47.570 --> 00:14:50.550
But we never imagined the two
topics would mesh like this in

00:14:50.550 --> 00:14:51.920
a very tragic way.

00:14:55.770 --> 00:14:57.580
SHANE SMITH: The freeing of
one of their own by the

00:14:57.580 --> 00:15:00.560
LeBarons protesting in Chihuahua
had sent a message

00:15:00.560 --> 00:15:01.600
to the narcos.

00:15:01.600 --> 00:15:03.150
They weren't going
to back down.

00:15:03.150 --> 00:15:04.390
They weren't going to submit.

00:15:04.390 --> 00:15:05.320
They were going to fight.

00:15:05.320 --> 00:15:07.250
But it didn't take "El
Rikin" long to send a

00:15:07.250 --> 00:15:08.500
message right back.

00:15:15.376 --> 00:15:18.750
BRENT LABARON: So yeah, this is
my cousin Benjamin's home.

00:15:18.750 --> 00:15:22.760
This "Rikin" guy actually
ordered the hit on him because

00:15:22.760 --> 00:15:24.440
of the stand we took.

00:15:24.440 --> 00:15:26.390
He was a serious criminal.

00:15:26.390 --> 00:15:29.570
I mean, famously, he got caught
on the American side of

00:15:29.570 --> 00:15:33.040
the border dressed as Mexican
military, had a shootout with

00:15:33.040 --> 00:15:34.620
the border guards, and
then came back here.

00:15:37.410 --> 00:15:39.060
So they came here
to his house.

00:15:45.120 --> 00:15:49.100
He showed up with 15, 20 guys,
two, three trucks--

00:15:49.100 --> 00:15:50.100
pickups.

00:15:50.100 --> 00:15:52.610
Benjamin and his family were
sleeping in the house when

00:15:52.610 --> 00:15:55.520
these guys come, surround the
house, breaking down his door.

00:15:55.520 --> 00:15:58.580
Ended up breaking pretty much
most of his windows out.

00:15:58.580 --> 00:16:01.830
There's still marks on the door
where they were trying to

00:16:01.830 --> 00:16:03.860
bash in with guns, whatever
they had.

00:16:03.860 --> 00:16:06.130
You know, those are sledgehammer
marks.

00:16:06.130 --> 00:16:09.180
And at that point, they had
threatened his family with a

00:16:09.180 --> 00:16:09.920
hand grenade.

00:16:09.920 --> 00:16:11.270
SHANE SMITH: So they said they'd
blow up the family with

00:16:11.270 --> 00:16:12.950
a grenade unless
he surrendered?

00:16:12.950 --> 00:16:13.910
BRENT LABARON: Unless
he opened the door.

00:16:13.910 --> 00:16:15.410
And so he opened the door.

00:16:15.410 --> 00:16:18.240
At that point, his
brother-in-law Luis come over

00:16:18.240 --> 00:16:19.490
to see what was going on.

00:16:19.490 --> 00:16:21.320
He literally showed
up in sandals.

00:16:21.320 --> 00:16:22.230
He came to the rescue.

00:16:22.230 --> 00:16:23.550
He was an innocent bystander.

00:16:23.550 --> 00:16:26.860
SHANE SMITH: So he came here
barefoot with no gun.

00:16:26.860 --> 00:16:27.210
BRENT LABARON: At all.

00:16:27.210 --> 00:16:28.980
SHANE SMITH: Against guys who
are armed with machine guns

00:16:28.980 --> 00:16:29.435
and grenades.

00:16:29.435 --> 00:16:29.700
BRENT LABARON: Yes.

00:16:29.700 --> 00:16:36.090
But they beat him and picked him
and Benjamin up and took

00:16:36.090 --> 00:16:39.860
them about two miles down the
road here and shot them both

00:16:39.860 --> 00:16:41.646
and left them on the
side of the road.

00:16:41.646 --> 00:16:42.480
SHANE SMITH: Jesus.

00:16:42.480 --> 00:16:46.850
So because "El Rikin" put the
hit out on Benjamin, it put

00:16:46.850 --> 00:16:49.830
enough domestic pressure here
that they would offer him up

00:16:49.830 --> 00:16:52.370
to the American authorities for
the Mexican incident where

00:16:52.370 --> 00:16:54.400
he was dressed as the military
with the border police.

00:16:54.400 --> 00:16:55.770
BRENT LABARON: Very much so.

00:16:55.770 --> 00:16:56.590
Very much so, yeah.

00:16:56.590 --> 00:16:59.380
Because I don't think they had
enough here to hold him here.

00:16:59.380 --> 00:17:01.760
So they actually shipped
him to the US.

00:17:01.760 --> 00:17:03.590
SHANE SMITH: And although "El
Rikin" was extradited to

00:17:03.590 --> 00:17:06.740
America for his firefights with
the border patrol, none

00:17:06.740 --> 00:17:09.089
of the other 20-plus men
involved in this double

00:17:09.089 --> 00:17:10.904
homicide have ever
been convicted.

00:17:16.210 --> 00:17:18.260
But the LeBarons
wouldn't quit.

00:17:18.260 --> 00:17:22.040
In fact, Julian LeBaron,
Benjamin's brother, has since

00:17:22.040 --> 00:17:24.690
taken up his dead sibling's
mantle of activism.

00:17:24.690 --> 00:17:24.900
SHANE SMITH: Shane.

00:17:24.900 --> 00:17:25.780
JULIAN LEBARON: Julian.

00:17:25.780 --> 00:17:27.569
SHANE SMITH: Good to meet you.

00:17:27.569 --> 00:17:28.750
JULIAN LEBARON: Well,
the main thing is,

00:17:28.750 --> 00:17:30.104
we want to be respected.

00:17:30.104 --> 00:17:32.692
And in Mexico, nobody's
respected.

00:17:32.692 --> 00:17:35.057
We're not respected by the
criminals, and we're not

00:17:35.057 --> 00:17:36.307
respected by the government.

00:17:41.540 --> 00:17:44.850
"This is for messing with
[INAUDIBLE]'s people" or some

00:17:44.850 --> 00:17:45.690
stupid shit.

00:17:45.690 --> 00:17:46.700
I don't remember what it was.

00:17:46.700 --> 00:17:48.330
And that's where they
found them.

00:17:48.330 --> 00:17:50.586
They shot them four times
in the head each.

00:17:50.586 --> 00:17:51.500
SHANE SMITH: Shit.

00:17:51.500 --> 00:17:53.400
JULIAN LEBARON: I think that
most of us felt really

00:17:53.400 --> 00:17:57.100
thankful that we found them,
because sometimes they'll take

00:17:57.100 --> 00:17:59.460
them and torture
them to death.

00:17:59.460 --> 00:18:02.070
People from our neighboring
communities participated in

00:18:02.070 --> 00:18:03.320
this murder.

00:18:09.494 --> 00:18:12.090
Those are some of the
people that are

00:18:12.090 --> 00:18:13.000
involved with this shit.

00:18:13.000 --> 00:18:13.750
SHANE SMITH: Really?

00:18:13.750 --> 00:18:15.450
Those guys are bad boys?

00:18:22.786 --> 00:18:24.036
SHANE SMITH: Jesus Christ.

00:18:27.870 --> 00:18:30.470
JULIAN LEBARON: 10 children
under the age of seven were

00:18:30.470 --> 00:18:34.740
left orphans when that
happened that night.

00:18:34.740 --> 00:18:37.775
My brother and his
brother-in-law, they were some

00:18:37.775 --> 00:18:39.850
of the most valuable people
in our community.

00:18:39.850 --> 00:18:41.940
This can never be acceptable.

00:18:41.940 --> 00:18:42.050
Never.

00:18:42.050 --> 00:18:46.750
Because if this is acceptable,
there's no future left.

00:18:46.750 --> 00:18:49.230
The community-- initially, what
we said is, for every

00:18:49.230 --> 00:18:50.673
person they kill from
our community,

00:18:50.673 --> 00:18:51.770
we'll kill 10 of them.

00:18:51.770 --> 00:18:53.561
Because we know who they are.

00:18:53.561 --> 00:18:56.090
And then we said, well, that's
not a solution, because then

00:18:56.090 --> 00:18:57.420
you become just like them.

00:19:02.170 --> 00:19:03.510
SHANE SMITH: So the sun
was going down.

00:19:03.510 --> 00:19:04.690
It was getting a little
bit late.

00:19:04.690 --> 00:19:06.600
And the LeBarons told us that
we should get back to our

00:19:06.600 --> 00:19:08.880
hotel before it got dark.

00:19:08.880 --> 00:19:11.840
We are going to a hotel that's
actually in the LeBaron

00:19:11.840 --> 00:19:13.970
colony, which hopefully will
be a little bit safer.

00:19:13.970 --> 00:19:16.270
But after you hear stories
like that, you just can't

00:19:16.270 --> 00:19:19.930
believe the fear of violence
that these people

00:19:19.930 --> 00:19:21.680
live under every day.

00:19:21.680 --> 00:19:23.800
It makes you paranoid to
hear stories like that.

00:19:23.800 --> 00:19:27.714
So we're going to go to our
hotel and lock ourselves in.

00:19:34.070 --> 00:19:37.930
This is a shrine to Jesus
Malverde, who's the patron

00:19:37.930 --> 00:19:41.900
saint of drug smugglers,
narcos.

00:19:41.900 --> 00:19:43.540
So we're going to
light a candle.

00:19:43.540 --> 00:19:46.190
This is freaking me out
because I'm very

00:19:46.190 --> 00:19:48.080
superstitious.

00:19:48.080 --> 00:19:49.160
That's him there.

00:19:49.160 --> 00:19:51.030
Patron saint of the
drug dealers.

00:19:51.030 --> 00:19:54.490
They all come in here, they
say a prayer, they write a

00:19:54.490 --> 00:19:57.910
prayer on here, and they say,
please let me get across the

00:19:57.910 --> 00:20:00.330
border with my drugs.

00:20:00.330 --> 00:20:03.400
Literally, religion about
drug dealers.

00:20:08.560 --> 00:20:10.650
Now, the whole time I was
hanging out with the LeBarons,

00:20:10.650 --> 00:20:13.200
I found myself wondering, how
do you actually protect

00:20:13.200 --> 00:20:16.590
yourself against narco lords
who employ whole armies of

00:20:16.590 --> 00:20:21.090
assassins whose sole job is
to kill their rivals?

00:20:21.090 --> 00:20:24.010
Well, the LeBarons started by
adopting military style

00:20:24.010 --> 00:20:26.940
tactics and setting up
checkpoints, roadblocks, and

00:20:26.940 --> 00:20:27.880
watchtowers.

00:20:27.880 --> 00:20:29.570
BRENT LABARON: We hit
a real big low

00:20:29.570 --> 00:20:30.740
when they killed Benjamin.

00:20:30.740 --> 00:20:34.255
It was a real big blow to
our entire community.

00:20:34.255 --> 00:20:38.170
I was really close
to Benjamin.

00:20:38.170 --> 00:20:39.980
Knew him really well.

00:20:39.980 --> 00:20:42.960
SHANE SMITH: After Benjamin was
killed, you've set up your

00:20:42.960 --> 00:20:45.010
own community watch, your
own night watch.

00:20:45.010 --> 00:20:47.680
And then you built this up, and
you have people watching

00:20:47.680 --> 00:20:48.460
every night.

00:20:48.460 --> 00:20:49.170
BRENT LABARON: Every night.

00:20:49.170 --> 00:20:50.070
So we have--

00:20:50.070 --> 00:20:51.120
SHANE SMITH: What are
you watching for?

00:20:51.120 --> 00:20:54.470
BRENT LABARON: Pretty much
suspicious vehicles.

00:20:54.470 --> 00:20:55.940
We pretty much know everybody.

00:20:55.940 --> 00:20:58.690
And so if it looks like a
vehicle I've never seen

00:20:58.690 --> 00:21:00.790
before, then it was
getting checked.

00:21:00.790 --> 00:21:03.370
SHANE SMITH: This watch hut
looks down on one of the main

00:21:03.370 --> 00:21:04.570
drug trafficking roads.

00:21:04.570 --> 00:21:05.730
BRENT LABARON: One
of them, yeah.

00:21:05.730 --> 00:21:07.400
SHANE SMITH: The only
people here with

00:21:07.400 --> 00:21:09.950
weapons are the criminals.

00:21:09.950 --> 00:21:10.570
BRENT LABARON: Pretty much.

00:21:10.570 --> 00:21:11.650
SHANE SMITH: The drug cartels.

00:21:11.650 --> 00:21:13.420
BRENT LABARON: Rumor got out
that we had high-powered

00:21:13.420 --> 00:21:15.840
rifles and snipers
and whatnot.

00:21:15.840 --> 00:21:18.170
SHANE SMITH: And .50 cals
up here and stuff.

00:21:18.170 --> 00:21:20.990
BRENT LABARON: Well, you know
how rumors can spread.

00:21:20.990 --> 00:21:22.640
Which was a benefit for us.

00:21:22.640 --> 00:21:22.955
SHANE SMITH: Yeah, it's good.

00:21:22.955 --> 00:21:23.270
It's a good rumor.

00:21:23.270 --> 00:21:25.570
BRENT LABARON: It was a really
good rumor for us, you know.

00:21:25.570 --> 00:21:29.770
I believe that the watchtower
is one of the key points to

00:21:29.770 --> 00:21:32.270
keeping the bad guys
away from our town.

00:21:32.270 --> 00:21:36.010
Also, the feds and the military
are in our town.

00:21:36.010 --> 00:21:36.930
This is their base.

00:21:36.930 --> 00:21:40.270
We actually had a roadblock, to
where there was one way in

00:21:40.270 --> 00:21:41.640
and one way out.

00:21:41.640 --> 00:21:44.260
SHANE SMITH: So you have
barricades, checkpoints, and

00:21:44.260 --> 00:21:44.930
watchtowers?

00:21:44.930 --> 00:21:46.040
BRENT LABARON: Yeah.

00:21:46.040 --> 00:21:49.220
I would say our valley right
here is quite a bit safer than

00:21:49.220 --> 00:21:50.330
a lot of areas--

00:21:50.330 --> 00:21:52.500
SHANE SMITH: Casas Grandes,
which is about 30 minutes

00:21:52.500 --> 00:21:55.510
away, they're still having
kidnappings and stuff there.

00:21:55.510 --> 00:21:56.520
BRENT LABARON: Here and there.

00:21:56.520 --> 00:21:59.890
Before, it was literally
two, three a week.

00:21:59.890 --> 00:22:00.750
SHANE SMITH: Wow.

00:22:00.750 --> 00:22:01.970
