You know, I remember his father
ran for President of

00:33:41.046 --> 00:33:42.400
the United States in '68.

00:33:42.400 --> 00:33:44.450
Or at least he was
a candidate.

00:33:44.450 --> 00:33:46.440
His citizenship was
questioned.

00:33:46.440 --> 00:33:49.190
Because he was born here in
Mexico, but he was born of

00:33:49.190 --> 00:33:50.510
American parents.

00:33:50.510 --> 00:33:53.770
SHANE SMITH: And do you think
that this craziness around the

00:33:53.770 --> 00:33:56.720
run-up to the election, is
that bringing too much

00:33:56.720 --> 00:33:57.630
attention, or?

00:33:57.630 --> 00:34:00.510
KELLY ROMNEY: I think one of the
reasons it's brought a lot

00:34:00.510 --> 00:34:03.490
of attention to here is because
of Mitt's position on

00:34:03.490 --> 00:34:04.250
illegal immigration.

00:34:04.250 --> 00:34:04.660
SHANE SMITH: Right.

00:34:04.660 --> 00:34:07.580
Now what's ironic about this
is that Mitt Romney, whose

00:34:07.580 --> 00:34:10.330
father was born in Mexico and
would be considered the poster

00:34:10.330 --> 00:34:12.710
child of the Dream Act, actually
has one of the

00:34:12.710 --> 00:34:15.230
staunchest views on immigration
in his already

00:34:15.230 --> 00:34:17.290
conservative Republican Party.

00:34:17.290 --> 00:34:18.730
MITT ROMNEY: And I've indicated
I would veto the

00:34:18.730 --> 00:34:21.600
Dream Act if provisions included
that people who are

00:34:21.600 --> 00:34:24.340
here illegally, if they go to
school here long enough, get a

00:34:24.340 --> 00:34:26.900
degree here, that they can
become permanent residents.

00:34:26.900 --> 00:34:29.030
I think that's a mistake.

00:34:29.030 --> 00:34:31.150
SHANE SMITH: Now, it seems a bit
weird for a person who's

00:34:31.150 --> 00:34:34.510
essentially a first generation
immigrant to have such harsh

00:34:34.510 --> 00:34:36.320
views on immigration.

00:34:36.320 --> 00:34:39.239
It's kind of like, "Methink
thy dost protest too much"

00:34:39.239 --> 00:34:41.420
kind of deal.

00:34:41.420 --> 00:34:44.699
And his own cousin Kelly, who
although he supports Mitt for

00:34:44.699 --> 00:34:46.489
president, thinks that
his position on

00:34:46.489 --> 00:34:48.280
immigration is wrong.

00:34:48.280 --> 00:34:50.610
KELLY ROMNEY: I think
he needs to change.

00:34:50.610 --> 00:34:54.150
Being born and raised in Mexico,
and especially since

00:34:54.150 --> 00:34:57.990
NAFTA, I think the United States
is partly responsible

00:34:57.990 --> 00:35:00.470
for the increase in illegal
immigration we have.

00:35:00.470 --> 00:35:00.840
SHANE SMITH: Right.

00:35:00.840 --> 00:35:02.710
So America makes policy.

00:35:02.710 --> 00:35:05.360
Then all of a sudden, northern
Mexico gets screwed up.

00:35:05.360 --> 00:35:06.260
KELLY ROMNEY: That's right.

00:35:06.260 --> 00:35:08.700
Give amnesty to those that are
out there that are working

00:35:08.700 --> 00:35:11.540
legitimately and have a job,
come up with a guest worker

00:35:11.540 --> 00:35:14.500
program, and let these people
go out there and work, and

00:35:14.500 --> 00:35:16.350
then come home and take
care of their family.

00:35:16.350 --> 00:35:17.530
Because basically, they're
starving to

00:35:17.530 --> 00:35:18.810
death here in Mexico.

00:35:18.810 --> 00:35:21.130
SHANE SMITH: In fact, it's so
bad that for many people,

00:35:21.130 --> 00:35:22.660
there's only really
two options.

00:35:22.660 --> 00:35:24.500
One, sneak into America.

00:35:24.500 --> 00:35:26.480
Or two, work for the cartels.

00:35:26.480 --> 00:35:28.790
You know, didn't some farmers
go up from the farms and go

00:35:28.790 --> 00:35:30.390
into the mountains and
start growing drugs?

00:35:30.390 --> 00:35:30.780
KELLY ROMNEY: Yeah.

00:35:30.780 --> 00:35:32.870
A lot of them have gone into the
mountain areas, and they

00:35:32.870 --> 00:35:33.560
grow drugs there.

00:35:33.560 --> 00:35:35.370
SHANE SMITH: And now we're
sitting here going, OK, well,

00:35:35.370 --> 00:35:35.920
what are we going to do?

00:35:35.920 --> 00:35:36.630
KELLY ROMNEY: What are
we going to do?

00:35:36.630 --> 00:35:37.160
Exactly.

00:35:37.160 --> 00:35:38.540
You know?

00:35:38.540 --> 00:35:40.280
I wish Mitt would make
contact with us.

00:35:40.280 --> 00:35:43.280
And I really think that
we could help him.

00:35:43.280 --> 00:35:45.520
SHANE SMITH: And as I would
later realize, contacting the

00:35:45.520 --> 00:35:48.140
Mexican side of his family would
probably be the last

00:35:48.140 --> 00:35:49.730
thing that Mitt Romney
would do.

00:35:49.730 --> 00:35:51.530
MITT ROMNEY: I think marijuana
should not be

00:35:51.530 --> 00:35:52.380
legal in this country.

00:35:52.380 --> 00:35:57.070
I believe it's a gateway drug
to other drug violations.

00:35:57.070 --> 00:36:00.440
The use of illegal drugs in
this country is leading to

00:36:00.440 --> 00:36:01.690
terrible consequences.

00:36:05.960 --> 00:36:08.250
SHANE SMITH: Now, we all know
Mitt Romney's stance on drugs.

00:36:08.250 --> 00:36:10.310
But it was interesting to hear
Kelly's thoughts on the drug

00:36:10.310 --> 00:36:13.640
war, considering it affects
him every day.

00:36:13.640 --> 00:36:16.050
KELLY ROMNEY: To me, this used
to be the most peaceful place

00:36:16.050 --> 00:36:17.010
in the world.

00:36:17.010 --> 00:36:17.410
Yeah, man.

00:36:17.410 --> 00:36:20.550
I used let my kids go to Nuevo
Casas Grandes, go to the

00:36:20.550 --> 00:36:22.990
shows, go to dances,
go to parties.

00:36:22.990 --> 00:36:25.890
But now, you keep close watch.

00:36:25.890 --> 00:36:29.500
And it all has to do with the
drug violence that it started.

00:36:29.500 --> 00:36:33.250
When they started the
war on drugs, the

00:36:33.250 --> 00:36:35.540
violence just escalated.

00:36:35.540 --> 00:36:37.470
Most of the problems
that we have around

00:36:37.470 --> 00:36:39.260
here are drug related.

00:36:39.260 --> 00:36:42.580
And there's been some
kidnappings and some killings

00:36:42.580 --> 00:36:45.080
from drug-related things.

00:36:45.080 --> 00:36:48.380
SHANE SMITH: Have there ever
been any Romneys kidnapped?

00:36:48.380 --> 00:36:50.510
KELLY ROMNEY: Yeah, my brother
was kidnapped three

00:36:50.510 --> 00:36:52.020
years ago in May.

00:36:52.020 --> 00:36:54.170
I think they kept him
for two days.

00:36:54.170 --> 00:36:56.030
Took him to a cave up
in the mountains.

00:36:56.030 --> 00:36:57.280
We paid a small ransom.

00:36:57.280 --> 00:36:58.400
It wasn't a lot.

00:36:58.400 --> 00:36:59.920
They were mainly punks.

00:36:59.920 --> 00:37:02.260
They weren't really
professionals.

00:37:02.260 --> 00:37:05.350
SHANE SMITH: And most of the
weapons that are here in

00:37:05.350 --> 00:37:07.350
Mexico are illegal weapons.

00:37:07.350 --> 00:37:09.370
And most of those illegal
weapons are

00:37:09.370 --> 00:37:10.580
coming from the States.

00:37:10.580 --> 00:37:11.380
KELLY ROMNEY: Yes.

00:37:11.380 --> 00:37:14.800
Fast and Furious, I'm sure
you heard about that.

00:37:14.800 --> 00:37:16.950
SHANE SMITH: Now, the Fast and
the Furious scandal he's

00:37:16.950 --> 00:37:20.320
talking about refers to a case
where the American government

00:37:20.320 --> 00:37:22.570
gave thousands of guns
to the cartels in

00:37:22.570 --> 00:37:23.640
order to track them.

00:37:23.640 --> 00:37:26.460
Then, they proceeded to lose
track of them until they

00:37:26.460 --> 00:37:29.930
surfaced again in the murder
cases of American agents.

00:37:29.930 --> 00:37:31.260
KELLY ROMNEY: What, did they
think they were going to be

00:37:31.260 --> 00:37:32.180
able to keep control of them?

00:37:32.180 --> 00:37:33.750
Or keep track of them?

00:37:33.750 --> 00:37:34.660
Nonsense.

00:37:34.660 --> 00:37:37.500
I don't know what in the world
they were thinking in sending

00:37:37.500 --> 00:37:40.470
all those weapons to Mexico.

00:37:40.470 --> 00:37:42.380
SHANE SMITH: And the Fast and
the Furious scandal is just

00:37:42.380 --> 00:37:44.640
one of many that have seriously
embarrassed the

00:37:44.640 --> 00:37:45.890
American government.

00:37:45.890 --> 00:37:49.480
Now, perhaps Mitt's hard-line
stance on issues like guns,

00:37:49.480 --> 00:37:52.430
immigration, and drugs
becomes more clear.

00:37:52.430 --> 00:37:55.160
Because even though his father
was born in Chihuahua, Mitt

00:37:55.160 --> 00:37:57.640
surely must want to distance
himself from the region.

00:37:57.640 --> 00:38:00.530
Because the region is
totally fucked up.

00:38:00.530 --> 00:38:02.950
And it's not the first time that
this has been the Romney

00:38:02.950 --> 00:38:04.050
strategy either.

00:38:04.050 --> 00:38:06.080
When his father ran for
president, both his

00:38:06.080 --> 00:38:09.450
citizenship and his Mormon
colony's polygamist roots were

00:38:09.450 --> 00:38:10.920
called into question.

00:38:10.920 --> 00:38:11.030
And.

00:38:11.030 --> 00:38:13.870
His run for the White House
didn't last too long.

00:38:13.870 --> 00:38:17.010
But Mitt Romney has to deal with
his family's polygamist

00:38:17.010 --> 00:38:21.730
past, kidnapping, drug wars,
and, in the extreme case of

00:38:21.730 --> 00:38:25.440
Ervil LeBaron, crazy Mormon
blood atonement.

00:38:25.440 --> 00:38:28.785
Now, having close familial ties
to all this shit does not

00:38:28.785 --> 00:38:30.450
a good presidential
candidate make.

00:38:33.750 --> 00:38:36.650
Being on the front lines of
this, what do you think are

00:38:36.650 --> 00:38:38.340
some of the solutions
to these problems?

00:38:38.340 --> 00:38:40.330
KELLY ROMNEY: Looking at it from
a perspective of someone

00:38:40.330 --> 00:38:43.250
living here, we say, well, why
don't they legalize it in the

00:38:43.250 --> 00:38:47.730
United States and cut out all
the violence in Mexico?

00:38:47.730 --> 00:38:50.680
As long as you have the swimming
pool over there, this

00:38:50.680 --> 00:38:52.476
is going to be the
diving board.

00:38:57.560 --> 00:38:59.260
SHANE SMITH: So as we began
our long drive back to the

00:38:59.260 --> 00:39:01.360
border, I had lots of time
to think about what

00:39:01.360 --> 00:39:03.120
we'd seen in Chihuahua.

00:39:03.120 --> 00:39:04.400
I thought about the
LeBarons and the

00:39:04.400 --> 00:39:05.640
war against the narcos.

00:39:05.640 --> 00:39:08.630
The kidnappings, the murders,
and the lengths they have to

00:39:08.630 --> 00:39:11.540
go to protect themselves
every day.

00:39:11.540 --> 00:39:13.980
I also thought about what Kelly
Romney had said about

00:39:13.980 --> 00:39:15.730
the US being the swimming
pool and Mexico

00:39:15.730 --> 00:39:17.010
being the diving board.

00:39:17.010 --> 00:39:20.200
And how similar all this is
to America's history with

00:39:20.200 --> 00:39:21.450
outlawing alcohol.

00:39:24.880 --> 00:39:28.030
So we're just approaching the
border here back into America.

00:39:28.030 --> 00:39:30.680
It feels like about a year
has passed since

00:39:30.680 --> 00:39:31.840
we were here last.

00:39:31.840 --> 00:39:35.500
As we were driving here from
Chihuahua, I was thinking

00:39:35.500 --> 00:39:38.030
about how prohibition in America
led to the rise of the

00:39:38.030 --> 00:39:40.640
mob, the Al Capones,
the Lucky Lucianos.

00:39:40.640 --> 00:39:43.410
Our war on drugs, our
prohibition against drugs, has

00:39:43.410 --> 00:39:44.350
caused the same thing.

00:39:44.350 --> 00:39:45.540
You see it down here.

00:39:45.540 --> 00:39:46.983
It's the sort of blunt
head to the hammer.

00:39:46.983 --> 00:39:48.350
It's the rule of the thug.

00:39:48.350 --> 00:39:50.120
You have $200 assassins.

00:39:50.120 --> 00:39:52.170
And as long as there's
prohibition,

00:39:52.170 --> 00:39:53.230
it's going to continue.

00:39:53.230 --> 00:39:54.665
The war on drugs is a failure.

00:39:54.665 --> 00:39:56.900
There's never been more drugs in
America, and they've never

00:39:56.900 --> 00:39:57.340
been cheaper.

00:39:57.340 --> 00:39:57.890
Or better.

00:39:57.890 --> 00:39:59.880
Or higher quality.

00:39:59.880 --> 00:40:02.150
And as we sat for hours at the
border waiting to get back

00:40:02.150 --> 00:40:05.150
into America, I thought about
the fact that Mitt Romney

00:40:05.150 --> 00:40:06.560
might just be the
next President

00:40:06.560 --> 00:40:07.520
of the United States.

00:40:07.520 --> 00:40:08.816
MITT ROMNEY: God
bless America.

00:40:08.816 --> 00:40:10.550
Thanks, you guys.

00:40:10.550 --> 00:40:13.010
SHANE SMITH: Now, polygamy and
kidnapping not withstanding,

00:40:13.010 --> 00:40:16.420
if he wins, he's going to have
some hard decisions to make

00:40:16.420 --> 00:40:18.550
about decriminalizing
drugs and fixing

00:40:18.550 --> 00:40:19.920
our immigration problem.

00:40:19.920 --> 00:40:23.620
Because if he doesn't, Mexico,
his Mormon brethren, and

00:40:23.620 --> 00:40:25.970
perhaps even his own flesh
and blood, are

00:40:25.970 --> 00:40:27.220
going to pay the price.

